@BookApi_HostAddress = http://localhost:5280

### ─── BOOKS CRUD ─────────────────────────────────────

### Get all books
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books
Accept: application/json

###

### Get book 1 (1984 - seeded)
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books/1
Accept: application/json

###

### Get book 2 (Brave New World - seeded)
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books/2
Accept: application/json

###

### Create a book with ONE author
POST {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Animal Farm",
  "year": 1945,
  "authorIds": [1]
}

###

### Create a book with TWO authors (many to many)
POST {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Co-authored Book",
  "year": 2024,
  "authorIds": [1, 2]
}

###

### Verify co-authored book has both authors
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books/4
Accept: application/json

###

### Update a book
PUT {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books/4
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Co-authored Book (Updated)",
  "year": 2025
}

###

### Verify update
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books/4
Accept: application/json

###

### Delete a book
DELETE {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books/4
Accept: application/json

###

### Verify book deleted (should return 404)
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books/4
Accept: application/json

###

### ─── AUTHORS CRUD ────────────────────────────────────

### Get all authors
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/authors
Accept: application/json

###

### Get author 1 (George Orwell - seeded)
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/authors/1
Accept: application/json

###

### Get author 2 (Aldous Huxley - seeded)
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/authors/2
Accept: application/json

###

### Create author 3
POST {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/authors
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Fyodor Dostoevsky",
  "country": "Russia"
}

###

### Create author 4
POST {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/authors
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Leo Tolstoy",
  "country": "Russia"
}

###

### Create author 5
POST {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/authors
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Franz Kafka",
  "country": "Czech"
}

###

### Delete an author
DELETE {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/authors/5
Accept: application/json

###

### Verify author deleted (should return 404)
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/authors/5
Accept: application/json

###

### ─── MANY TO MANY - BASIC ───────────────────────────

### Get all books by author 1
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books/by-author/1
Accept: application/json

###

### Get all books by author 2
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books/by-author/2
Accept: application/json

###

### Create book shared by both seeded authors
POST {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Shared World",
  "year": 2023,
  "authorIds": [1, 2]
}

###

### Author 1 should show shared book in their list
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/authors/1
Accept: application/json

###

### Author 2 should also show shared book
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/authors/2
Accept: application/json

###

### ─── MANY TO MANY - VOLUME ──────────────────────────

### Create book with 3 authors
POST {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Three Authors Book",
  "year": 2023,
  "authorIds": [1, 2, 3]
}

###

### Create book with 4 authors
POST {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Four Authors Book",
  "year": 2023,
  "authorIds": [1, 2, 3, 4]
}

###

### Verify 4 authors appear on book
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books/by-author/4
Accept: application/json

###

### ─── MANY TO MANY - EDGE CASES ─────────────────────

### Create book with NO authors (empty array)
POST {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Orphan Book",
  "year": 2020,
  "authorIds": []
}

###

### Create book with non-existent authorId (should fail gracefully)
POST {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Ghost Author Book",
  "year": 2021,
  "authorIds": [999]
}

###

### Create book with duplicate authorIds (same author twice)
POST {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Duplicate Author Test",
  "year": 2022,
  "authorIds": [1, 1]
}

###

### ─── MANY TO MANY - RELATIONSHIP INTEGRITY ─────────

### Create book linked to authors 3 and 4
POST {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Book To Delete Author From",
  "year": 2022,
  "authorIds": [3, 4]
}

###

### Confirm book linked to author 3
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books/by-author/3
Accept: application/json

###

### Confirm book linked to author 4
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books/by-author/4
Accept: application/json

###

### Delete author 3 (cascade removes BookAuthor rows)
DELETE {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/authors/3
Accept: application/json

###

### Books by author 3 should now be empty
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books/by-author/3
Accept: application/json

###

### Author 4 should still be linked (not affected by author 3 delete)
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books/by-author/4
Accept: application/json

###

### ─── MANY TO MANY - CASCADE DELETE BOOK ────────────

### Create book linked to authors 4 and 5
POST {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Last Book Before Delete",
  "year": 2024,
  "authorIds": [4, 5]
}

###

### Confirm book linked to author 4
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books/by-author/4
Accept: application/json

###

### Delete the book (BookAuthor rows should cascade delete)
DELETE {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books/9
Accept: application/json

###

### Author 4 still exists but that book gone from their list
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/authors/4
Accept: application/json

###

### Author 5 same check
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/authors/5
Accept: application/json

###

### ─── CROSS REFERENCE FINAL CHECK ───────────────────

### Author 1 - should appear in many books
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/authors/1
Accept: application/json

###

### Author 2 - same
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/authors/2
Accept: application/json

###

### Full books list - verify all authors arrays populated
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/books
Accept: application/json

###

### Full authors list - verify all bookTitles arrays populated
GET {{BookApi_HostAddress}}/api/authors
Accept: application/json

###